🎤 🏆 1. Demo Structure (Golden Flow)

👉 Your demo should follow this story:

Problem
Solution
Live Demo
Key Features
Wrap-up
🎯 🧠 2. What to SAY (Script)
🎬 Step 1: Opening (10–15 sec)

Say:

“In many colleges, students face issues like hostel problems, IT issues, or academic queries, but there is no centralized system to track and resolve them efficiently.”

💡 Step 2: Your Solution

“So we built a role-based helpdesk system where students can raise tickets and admins can manage and resolve them based on their department.”

🚀 🖥️ 3. LIVE DEMO FLOW (very important)
👉 Step A: Show Landing Page

Say:

“This is the entry point where users can choose their role.”

👉 Click Student

👉 Step B: Student creates ticket

Say:

“Students can raise issues by selecting category and providing details.”

👉 Fill:

Title: WiFi not working
Category: IT
Student ID: 1

👉 Click Create

Say:

“The ticket is now created and routed based on category.”

👉 Step C: Switch to Admin

👉 Go back → Click Admin

Say:

“Admins can view and manage all tickets in a centralized dashboard.”

👉 Step D: Show Dashboard

👉 Point to:

Stats cards
Table

Say:

“Here we can see ticket statistics and all incoming requests.”

👉 Step E: Assign Ticket

👉 Click Assign

Enter:

1 (or admin ID)

Say:

“Admins can take ownership of tickets and move them into progress.”

👉 Toast appears

👉 Step F: Filter

👉 Select:

Open / In Progress

Say:

“We also support filtering to easily track ticket status.”

👉 Step G: Dark Mode (wow moment)

👉 Click dark mode 🌙

Say:

“We also added a modern UI with dark mode for better usability.”

👉 (Pause 1 second — let them react)

🧠 🏁 4. Key Features (quick bullets)

Say:

“Key features include:”

Role-based dashboards
Category-based ticket routing
Admin assignment system
Real-time status tracking
Clean and responsive UI
🧾 🎯 5. Wrap-up (closing line)

Say:

“This system improves transparency and ensures faster issue resolution in institutions.”

⚠️ 🚫 Common Mistakes (avoid these)
Don’t say:
“This is simple project” ❌
“We didn’t implement login” ❌

👉 Instead say:

“We focused on core functionality and scalable design.”

🧠 💡 Pro Tips (VERY IMPORTANT)
1. Keep demo under 3–4 minutes

👉 Don’t over explain

2. Always show working flow

👉 Create → View → Assign → Filter

3. Prepare data BEFORE demo

Create:

2 students
2 admins
3 tickets

👉 So UI looks alive

4. Speak slowly and clearly

👉 Confidence > complexity

🏆 Final Winning Line

End with:

“This can be extended with authentication, notifications, and analytics in a production environment.”

🔥 This line = interviewer impressed


docker run -d \
  --name helpdesk-db \
  -e MYSQL_ROOT_PASSWORD=helpdesk \
  -e MYSQL_DATABASE=helpdesk \
